	<pb facs="liv_001808_0001" n="0001"/><!-- Change both @facs and @n -->
	<!-- Start each page with a <pb> formatted as above -->

<!-- If this is a letter or similar with an opener (with content such as dateline and/or salute) add it. For example: -->
<opener>
<lb/><add place="over-text margintop" rend="right"><figure><head>13</head><figDesc>Sticker over letter</figDesc></figure></add>
<lb/><dateline rend="right"><placeName><settlement type="village">Kongone</settlement></placeName> <date when="1862-07-30">30<hi rend="underline">th</hi> July 1862</date></dateline>     
<lb/> 
<lb/><salute>My Dear Sir</salute>
</opener>
<lb/><p><space extent="11" unit="chars"/>In coming down
<lb/>we ran aground twice after
<lb/>you left us. The prospect
<lb/>of finding the <unclear cert="medium">river</unclear> still
<lb/>lower a month hence made
<lb/>us almost conclude that
<lb/>it will be better to spend
<lb/>the months between August
<lb/>&amp; November in boat
<lb/>exploration of the  <placeName><geogName type="river">Rovuma</geogName></placeName> 
<lb/>than in slowly threading   
                
    <pb facs="liv_001808_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/>our way up <placeName><geogName type="river">Zambesi</geogName></placeName> <unclear cert="medium">&amp;</unclear>      
<lb/><placeName><geogName type="river">Shire</geogName></placeName>. It is not quite decided
<lb/>yet but we must go to
<lb/><placeName><geogName type="island">Johanna</geogName></placeName> for though the
<lb/>Ariel called she had no
<lb/><orgName><placeName><geogName type="island">Johanna</geogName></placeName> crew</orgName> with her
<lb/>and was on her way to
<lb/>the <placeName><region>Cape</region></placeName>. We parted with
<lb/>our incorrigibles &amp; got a 
<lb/>carpenter &amp; quartermaster -
<lb/>instead: we are now getting
<lb/>ready for sea. In the mail
<lb/>I see one letter for you. 
<lb/>Please to send forward

    <pb facs="liv_001808_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/>the mail for the Mission
<lb/><unclear cert="medium"><persName>Vianna</persName></unclear><!-- I cannot make out this word. It could be the name of a place or an organisation. JM --><!-- This is my best guess. We can research this later. AW -->  will do it at their
<lb/>expense.</p>
<lb/><p><space extent="3" unit="chars"/><persName>Captain Oldfield</persName> said that
<lb/>the <persName>Baron</persName> had grumbled to the
<lb/>men of war at your having
<lb/>published a paper. <space extent="4" unit="chars"/>I
<lb/>understood that you were
<lb/>perfectly free to do so and
<lb/>think you had better let
<lb/>your friends know the
<lb/>footing on which you 
<lb/>went in case the <persName>Baron</persName>
<lb/>should say publicly that
<lb/>you had broken your
<lb/>engagement. I give you
    
    <pb facs="liv_001808_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/>this hint as the <term type="people">Germans</term> will
<lb/>be sure to appropriate all the
<lb/>credit to themselves if they can.
<lb/>If you go to <placeName><region>Gorongoza</region></placeName> look
<lb/>well after the inscriptions
<lb/>and in <placeName><settlement type="village">Manica</settlement></placeName> it will be well
<lb/>to ascertain the exact gold 
<lb/>bearing stratum. Hoping that
<lb/>you will keep your health
<lb/>&amp; be protected by our
<lb/>Almighty Father</p>
<lb/><closer rend="center"><salute>I am &amp;c.</salute>
<lb/><signed><persName>David Livingstone</persName></signed>
<lb/><space dim="vertical" extent="5" unit="lines"/>
<lb/><address><addrLine/><persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> <choice><abbr>R.</abbr><expan>Richard</expan></choice> Thornton</persName></address>
</closer>

